Finally, besides works on neutrino oscillation, the DC collaboration also released many other interesting physics analysis, such as a test of Lorentz violation~\cite{12DCLo}, ortho-positronium observation~\cite{14DCPs}, and muon capture on light isotopes~\cite{15DCMuCap}.

\section{Summary}
\label{sec:Summary}
The reactor measurement of $\theta_{13}$ is a very important part of the neutrino oscillation studies. 
Double Chooz initiated the field from the era of the Chooz experiment. 
It showed the first indication of the reactor neutrino deficit at a baseline $\sim $1~km and is measuring $\theta_{13}$ using high quality data and analysis techniques. 
In the near future, it will present a precise $\theta_{13}$ using the near+far detector data. 
The high precision $\theta_{13}$ value measured by reactor experiments will become an indispensable piece of information in the next decades when the mass hierarchy and leptonic CP violation are to be measured and insights into the nature are expected to be deepened. 


