\caption{\small{The reactor neutrino spectrum ``bump''. Left: Ratio between the best-fit and non-oscillated spectra for both n-Gd and n-H analysis, where a structure (``bump'') can be seen between 4 and 6~MeV. Right: Zoom of the prompt IBD energy spectra for the Gd-III and H-II selection methods, where a exponential fit was done without taking into account the bins between 4 and 6~MeV, showing an excess in this region. The inset shows the correlation of the excess with the reactor power and analysis method (statistics).}}
\label{fig:SpecExcess}
